Today is international nurses day, a day set aside to celebrate the men and women considered front line healthcare workers. This year's celebration comes right in the middle of the global coronavirus pandemic that has ground the world to a halt. Its the day that marks the contribution that nurses make to society gives the world a chance to reflect on the services offered by healthcare givers in times of infirmity. Let's speak to Seth Panyako who is the secretary-general of the Kenyan union of nurses on the importance of nurses as frontline health care workers